         <abstract>
            <p>The author deems warrants to be securities in their own right and a form of long-term capital. Warrants can be used alone as a means of raising equity capital or as a substitute for stock dividends. How well a proposed warrant serves the corporate interest can be analyzed in terms of a new concept called the "break-even common price."</p>
